2.2.1 Trade Mechanism for Malicious Agents The buyer might maliciously punish the seller by  choosing the outcome (b) when the true state is H. The following notion quantifies the consideration that a player is not  indifferent to the private surpluses of others.
If Alice misreports LA > LT A, then Bob can ensure himself the bonus (which is always strictly preferable than reaching Stage 3) by challenging with LA = LT A, and so whenever Bob gets the bonus Alice gains the worst of all payoffs.
Intuitively this means that in equilibrium each player will choose his best action at each point 